cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information theoretic security and its application to broadcast channels with confidential messages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses cryptographic concepts such as hash functions, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses random coding arguments, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the decoding error probability, which could place it in cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
